# TAMAC Implementation Logging

## Read order (do not load everything)

1. **[cisco.mdc](../cisco.mdc)** — source of truth index, hard rules, quick reference
2. **[docs/PROGRESS.md](../docs/PROGRESS.md)** — what's done / what's next
3. **Latest [docs/logs/](../docs/logs/)** — actual commands and verified output
4. **One [docs/design/](../docs/design/) file** — only the topic needed (routing, ports, security, etc.)

## After major milestones

1. Update `docs/PROGRESS.md`
2. Add `docs/logs/NN-description.md` with commands + CLI output
3. If design changed, update the relevant `docs/design/*.md` file

**No Procurement department.** Never VLAN 60. Built reality in logs wins over design docs.
